		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_WAY_OF_THE_PILGRIM_DESCRIPTION">
			<Text>Raiders of the Lost Ark</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_WAY_OF_THE_PILGRIM_HELP">
			<Text>In the holy texts, it speaks of a vessel used to carry holy relics in the days of old. So many artifacts resided in the coffer that the latent power was enough for it to perform miracles long after they had been removed.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]If we could recover the ark, our power would be magnified without limit!</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_WAY_OF_THE_PILGRIM_HELP_CHOICE_1">
			<Text>Invoke {1_YieldCost} of new doctrine, causing your Temples and the Reliquary to generate +2 [ICON_TOURISM] Tourism.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_WAY_OF_THE_PILGRIM_HELP_CHOICE_2">
			<Text>Use {1_YieldCost} to spread word of your success in the quest. When a [ICON_CITIZEN] Citizen is born, the City receives a boost of 10 [ICON_TOURISM] Tourism (scaling with Era).</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_WAY_OF_THE_PILGRIM_HELP_CHOICE_3">
			<Text>Invoke {1_YieldCost} of new doctrine, causing your Buildings purchased with [ICON_PEACE] Faith and the Reliquary to generate +3 [ICON_TOURISM] Tourism.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_WAY_OF_THE_PILGRIM_HELP_CHOICE_4">
			<Text>Reveal {1_YieldCost} worth of religious mysteries. The Reliquary increases [ICON_TOURISM] Tourism by 20%.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_WAY_OF_THE_PILGRIM_HELP_CHOICE_5">
			<Text>In the final stage of the quest for the book, all [ICON_DIPLOMAT] Civil Servants generate +2 [ICON_PEACE] Faith and +2 [ICON_TOURISM] Tourism.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_WAY_OF_THE_PILGRIM_HELP_CHOICE_6">
			<Text>Bring together {1_YieldCost} to complete the quest. Cities convert 10% of [ICON_GOLD] Gold to [ICON_TOURISM] Tourism when purchasing.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_WAY_OF_THE_PILGRIM_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_1">
			<Text>Where do we even begin? We need to study the ancient records, and find out everything we can about the ark!</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_WAY_OF_THE_PILGRIM_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_2">
			<Text>*Study into the central tenets of our belief have formalised the treatment of relics*[NEWLINE]Nothing is ever lost. Long after the body has left a place, the soul lingers. Such is the way of nature.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_WAY_OF_THE_PILGRIM_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_3">
			<Text>Our hunt for the relics of the world must redouble in effort if we are to uncover this holy of holies!</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_WAY_OF_THE_PILGRIM_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_4">
			<Text>Success at last! Atop a weathered peak, a ruined shrine dating to the era of the ark has been uncovered. The shrine contains many relics and clues as to the location of the ark.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_WAY_OF_THE_PILGRIM_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_5">
			<Text>The scrolls are extensive. In order to transcribe all of them would take our priests an enormous amount of time. Perhaps we can find a more efficient way using our sophisticated infrastructure...</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_WAY_OF_THE_PILGRIM_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_6">
			<Text>At last, the artifact of all our pain is in our possession! The ark is as beautiful as promised, even now I can feel its power! We are unstoppable!</Text>
		</Row>
